The paper deals with entity alignment in knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an enhanced alignment model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
